tip.text: Seafood with ouzo sauce was just great; the first Greek restaurant I've visited that understands that main courses don't need to be loaded and overwhelmed with carbs.
The winding drive up is not that intimidating, simply drive cautiously and not too quickly. Definitely worth a visit for spectacular views of the Ionian Sea and even Albania.
The panna cotta and cheesecake are HIGHLY HIGHLY recommended. Had a lovely chat with Nikolas the young pastry chef.
The Fat Duck starter is sublime
Babi Rock Anthem is great for sharing with a group of 4-5 people.
